 pet form of the female personal name <i>Pernel</i>, see   Parnell  ."]},{"name":"Pernell","meanings":["English (Middlesex and Warwickshire): variant of   Parnell  . This form of the surname is rare in Britain and Ireland."]},{"name":"Purnell","meanings":["English: variant of   Parnell  ."]},{"name":"Pennell","meanings":["English (especially southeastern):","metronym from the Middle English female personal name <i>Pennel</i> (an assimilated form of   Parnell  ).","habitational name from Penn Hall in Pensax (Worcestershire), or from either of two places called Penhill in Devon and Yorkshire, or possibly from Pendle in Lancashire. All of the placenames probably derive from British <i>penn</i> ‘head’ + Old English <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’."]}]},{"name":"Catherine","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."],"variants":[{"name":"Catheryn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Katherine","meanings":["Pet form of   Katherine  , derived from the pet form   Kit   + the hypocoristic suffix <i>-y</i>. It is also used as an independent given name."]},{"name":"Catharin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathrine","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathryn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathrin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Catharine","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":32,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English